HEADWORD: Crossbeam
<hw>Cross"beam`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦emac⟧m`)</pr>. <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A girder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A beam laid across the bitts, to
which the cable is fastened when riding at anchor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cross-bearer</ent>⟦br⟧
